macro ArCH4.expm

*     Argon (93%)  CH4 (7%)   15 mm
*     0 degre C; 1 Atm; 1.709 mg/cm3
*
*     pion 3 GeV/c
*
*     F. Harris et al. NIM 107 (p.413) 1973
*

* distribution of the energy deposit
*
* (from 0.0 keV to 8.0 keV by bin of 0.2 keV --> 40 bins) 
*
nbin=40
vector/create vect([nbin])

**NB: the data are directly entered in mm, and normalized after

vector/input vect _
     3    4   10   19   35   64   91  109  140  163 _
   164  160  138  130  115  103   89   76   56   45 _
    37   30   27   22   20   15   13   12   10   11 _
    10    8    6    7    6    5    4    3    5    2

* renormalization ! (0.96 according the overflows in our simulation)
factor=0.96/$SIGMA(VSUM(vect))
vec/op/vscale vect [factor] vect
		    
dE=0.2e-3
Emin= 0.0
Emax= [Emin]+[nbin]*[dE]		     
create/1dhisto 1 'Ar-CH4  pion 3GeV/c' [nbin] [Emin] [Emax]
put/contents 1 vect
   
*option logy
h/pl 1

* save histo
*
*h/file 1 expmdat.paw ! n
*hrout 0
 
return 	     
